# Constant Fold DateTime Functions

## Description

Evaluates date/time functions with all-constant arguments at plan
time. DATE_TRUNC, EXTRACT, and date arithmetic on constants are
replaced with literal results.

**When to apply**: A datetime function has all constant arguments
(no column references, no non-deterministic functions like NOW()).

## Implementation

```rust
rw!("constant-fold-date-trunc";
    "(date-trunc ?unit ?ts)" =>
    "(literal (eval-date-trunc ?unit ?ts))"
    if is_constant("?unit") if is_constant("?ts")
),
rw!("constant-fold-extract";
    "(extract ?field ?ts)" =>
    "(literal (eval-extract ?field ?ts))"
    if is_constant("?field") if is_constant("?ts")
),
rw!("constant-fold-date-add";
    "(date-add ?date ?interval)" =>
    "(literal (eval-date-add ?date ?interval))"
    if is_constant("?date") if is_constant("?interval")
),
```

## Test Cases

```sql
-- Positive: DATE_TRUNC of constant
SELECT DATE_TRUNC('month', TIMESTAMP '2024-06-15 10:30:00');
-- Folded to: '2024-06-01 00:00:00'

-- Positive: EXTRACT of constant
SELECT EXTRACT(YEAR FROM DATE '2024-06-15');
-- Folded to: 2024

-- Negative: NOW() is non-deterministic
SELECT DATE_TRUNC('day', NOW());
-- Cannot fold: NOW() changes per invocation
```

## References

- functions.toml: DATE_TRUNC, EXTRACT marked constant_foldable = true
- Note: NOW(), CURRENT_TIMESTAMP are NOT constant_foldable
